{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/pulls/1511","id":753815603,"node_id":"PR_kwDOB-j9wM4s7lAz","html_url":"https://github.com/doccano/doccano/pull/1511","diff_url":"https://github.com/doccano/doccano/pull/1511.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/doccano/doccano/pull/1511.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1511","number":1511,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"Support nested named entity recognition, relation labeling, RTL language, improve speed and grapheme mode","user":{"login":"Hironsan","id":6737785,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Mzc3ODU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6737785?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan","html_url":"https://github.com/Hironsan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hironsan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"## Nested mode\r\n\r\n![](https://i.gyazo.com/09e01d9152cad820238acbc52f4be3fc.gif)\r\n\r\nOf course, you are able to annotate text without using nested mode.\r\n\r\n## Relation Labeling\r\n\r\n![](https://i.gyazo.com/79b6c31898c009629d22adc1362a2858.png)\r\n\r\n## RTL Language\r\n\r\n![](https://i.gyazo.com/02cc980a61ede7196029a2d84311ecd5.gif)\r\n\r\nIn the case of mixed RTL and LTR Language:\r\n\r\n![](https://i.gyazo.com/bf2d0293562b805072955a4ec913a46f.gif)\r\n\r\n## Grapheme mode\r\n\r\nIn JavaScript, there is not always a one-to-one relationship between string characters and what a user would call a separate visual \"letter\". Some symbols are represented by several characters. This can cause issues when you annotate the part of the text in sequence labeling.\r\n\r\nFor example, emoji characters like \"üå∑\",\"üéÅ\",\"üí©\",\"üòú\" and \"üëç\" are represented by two JavaScript characters each (high surrogate and low surrogate). That is,\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n\"üå∑\".length == 2\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe combined emoji is even longer:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n\"üè≥Ô∏è‚Äçüåà\".length == 6\r\n```\r\n\r\nTherefore, If your text includes such characters, the start/end offset indicates codepoint offset which is different from a \"visual offset\".\r\n\r\nSo, I implemented the \"Grapheme mode\" which counts the character per grapheme cluster. As an example, let's say you select the text as follows:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6737785/136881000-bed55db1-4407-4511-a4be-89692e2158c3.png)\r\n\r\nWith the grapheme mode, the offset is `(1, 3)`. On the other hand, without the mode, the offset is `(4, 12)` because it counts the codepoints.\r\n\r\n## Large Document\r\n\r\nI introduced the virtual rendering system to handle a large document. Now, we are able to annotate it(I tested about 1,000,000 characters document).","created_at":"2021-10-08T08:18:15Z","updated_at":"2022-01-27T09:33:27Z","closed_at":"2021-10-20T04:32:40Z","merged_at":"2021-10-20T04:32:40Z","merge_commit_sha":"15272db5632cb80b69ac797979c36b1e8588440f","assignee":null,"assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/pulls/1511/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/pulls/1511/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1511/comments","statuse